All Aspects To Design Distributed Web Applications
---------------------------------------------------

Defining Large Scale System
	- Huge amounts of data.
	- Concurrent users
	- Scalability Requirements
	- Throughput Requirements.

Distributed Systems
	- Microservices Archeteture
	- Serverless Archeteture

CAP (Consistency Availablity Partitioning) Theorem
	- You can have only two features out of three when you want to create a distrubuted archeteture 

Message Queues
	- Event Sourcing
	- message Queues

